## 3. Layer 2: Tool Connectivity — MCP

**"Everything is an MCP tool."** This is the core CASCI platform principle.

Every data source and algorithm in CASCI is exposed as an MCP tool with a standardized signature:
- **Input:** typed parameters
- **Output:** typed return value
- **Error:** structured error that agents can handle gracefully

### MCP Tool Categories

```
casci-platform/
└── mcp_tools/
    ├── sql_tools/           SQL Server (TenantDB) queries — read-only
    │   ├── demand_tools     get_baseline_demand, find_similar_events
    │   ├── supply_tools     get_inventory_position, get_sourcing_constraints
    │   └── financial_tools  get_unit_cost, get_carrying_cost_rate
    │
    ├── graph_tools/         Neo4j queries — Phase 3
    │   ├── product_tools    get_product_substitutes (KG), get_product_graph
    │   ├── supplier_tools   find_alternate_suppliers, get_supplier_network
    │   └── impact_tools     get_customers_affected_by_supplier
    │
    ├── algorithm_tools/     Blue Ridge algorithm wrappers
