### 6.4 Data Flow Diagram

| Agent | Reads from State | DB Tables Queried | Writes to State |
|-------|-----------------|------------------|----------------|
| Orchestrator | `event` (all fields) | None | `current_step`, `messages` |
| Demand Decomposition | `event.sku_id`, `event.discount_pct`, `event.customer_id`, `event.start_date` | `demand_history`, `deal`, `event_prod_loc_cust_uplift`, `product` | `demand_decomposition` |
| Supply Constraint | `event.sku_id`, `event.location_id`, `event.start_date` | `product_sourcing_network`, `approved_order`, `enterprise_settings`, location capacity tables | `supply_constraints` |
| Scenario Generator | `demand_decomposition` (full), `supply_constraints` (full) | None — LLM reasoning only | `scenarios` |
| Financial Impact | `scenarios`, `event.sku_id`, `event.customer_id` | `product` (unit_cost), customer + pricing tables (margin), `enterprise_settings` (carrying_cost_rate) | `financial_impacts` |
| Present to Planner | `scenarios`, `financial_impacts`, `demand_decomposition.confidence`, `errors` | None | `messages` (final trace) |

**All database access is read-only against TenantDB.** No agent writes directly to any table.

